Description: Length of two strand cord of wool; one strand dull red the other dark yellow; both ends frayings; a join consists of one end knotted through a loop about a third of the way down; red strand is made of 6 threads (S spun Z ply) and the yellow is made of 8 threads; probably a head ornament, almost certainly the draw cord from a sprang hair net
Curator's comments: Unreg. 120; found in drawer of unnumbered textiles in cupbaord P
